lass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break\";s:7:\"content\";s:2146:\"<header><p>It is an @name or @variable of transition layer, point which you gave before in a some function. How you should do it, see in structure function.</p></header><p>If you assigned a name in [markup]scene.repeat[/markup]</p><pre class=\"  language-javascript\"><code class=\"  language-javascript\">scene<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">repeat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> transform<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">scale</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0.6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0.4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0.6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> scaling <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre><p>for a layer your @variable_name in this function should looks like <strong><em>scaling{index}</em></strong> where index is ( integer ) number of collection. Scan by [markup]scene.var[/markup] the <strong><em>scaling</em> </strong>so you will understand using of index. Other way your @variable_name should be just an <strong><em>scaling</em></strong>.</p><div class=\"row\"><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">string</i></p></div><div class=\"row\"><p>Required</p></div>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:5:\"class\";s:5:\"clear\";}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 \";s:7:\"content\";s:15:\"<h3>Events</h3>\";}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break\";s:7:\"content\";s:607:\"<header><p>States which call callback.</p><p>Available states: <i class=\"lighting\">BEFORE</i>, <i class=\"lighting\">AFTER</i>, <i class=\"lighting\">ENTER</i>, <i class=\"lighting\">UPDATE</i></p></header><p>Events make single call the callback: <i class=\"lighting\">BEFORE</i>, <i class=\"lighting\">AFTER</i>, <i class=\"lighting\">ENTER</i>.</p><p><i class=\"lighting\">UPDATE </i>state call the callback every scroll by reaching the appropriate space.</p><p> </p><p>You can join states toghether.</p><p> </p><div class=\"row\"><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">string</i></p></div><div class=\"row\"><p>Required</p></div>\";}i:6;O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:5:\"class\";s:5:\"clear\";}i:7;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 \";s:7:\"content\";s:17:\"<h3>Callback</h3>\";}i:8;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break\";s:7:\"content\";s:312:\"<header><p>A function which is called.</p></header><p>The function returns <i class=\"lighting\">progress </i><i class=\"lighting\">state </i><i class=\"lighting\">var</i></p><p>[js]function(e){}[/js]</p><div class=\"row\"><p> </p><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">function</i></p></div><div class=\"row\"><p>Required</p></div>\";}i:9;O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:5:\"class\";s:5:\"clear\";}i:10;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:221:\"<h2>Example</h2>\n[js]scene.setPoint( 0.5, 0,bueno );\nscene.is( (string) bueno, (string) ENTER, BEFORE, function(e){\n  console.log(e);\n});\nscene.is( (string) bueno, (string) UPDATE, function(e){\n  console.log(e);\n});\n[/js]\";}}}}}');
