(1000002, 24, 'es_builder_output_backup', 'a:2:{i:0;a:2:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:4:\"cols\";s:8:\"children\";a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:148:\"<h2 class=\"title\">Selectors</h2><p>Top and bottom selector can moving by manipulate value in object which you can join with enedScroll function.</p>\";}}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"cols specification\";s:8:\"children\";a:5:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"col-xsmall-8 title\";s:7:\"content\";s:57:\"<p> </p><header><h3>Specification</h3></header><p> </p>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 \";s:7:\"content\";s:20:\"<h3>Description</h3>\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 \";s:7:\"content\";s:232:\"<header><p>Contains 2 values which are used. Value with key bigger than 1 is ignored.</p></header><div class=\"row\"><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">object</i></p></div><div class=\"row\"><p>Default <i class=\"lighting\">[0,0]</i></p></div>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:5:\"class\";s:5:\"clear\";}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:416:\"<h3>Examples</h3><p><img src=\"http://localhost/enedScroll%20-%20build/docs/index.php/orginal/selectors_example_1.png\" alt=\"selectors example 1\" /></p><p><img src=\"http://localhost/enedScroll%20-%20build/docs/index.php/orginal/selectors_example_2.png\" alt=\"selectors example 2\" /></p><p><img src=\"http://localhost/enedScroll%20-%20build/docs/index.php/orginal/selectors_example_3.png\" alt=\"selectors example 3\" /></p>\";}}}}i:1;a:2:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:4:\"cols\";s:8:\"children\";a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:145:\"<h2 class=\"title\">Visual</h2><p>Options which belong to visualisation. You can specifics css attributes when you use visual by these options.</p>\";}}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"cols specification\";s:8:\"children\";a:2:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"col-xsmall-8 title\";s:7:\"content\";s:40:\"<header><h3>Default values</h3></header>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:439:\"<p>show_selectors: <strong>false</strong>,<br />name_selectors: <strong>\'\'</strong>,<br />color_top_selector: <strong>#1233d8</strong>‚,<br />color_bottom_selector: <strong>#0cd2c9</strong>‚,<br />show_trigger: <strong>false</strong>,<br />color_trigger: <strong>orange</strong>‚,<br />zIndex_selectors: <strong>9999</strong>‚,<br />zIndex_trigger: <strong>9999</strong>‚,<br />scene_position: <strong>relative</strong></p>\";}}}}}'),
(1000003, 26, 'es_builder_output_backup', 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:4:\"cols\";s:8:\"children\";a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:664:\"<h2>Description</h2><p>Trigger calls events during scrolling on scene. The element contains 2 attributes. Name and margin top. You have to create trigger and add to enedScroll function. It should looks like example below.</p><pre class=\" language-javascript\"><code class=\" language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> trigger <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">enedScroll<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Trigger</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span> @name<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> @marginTop <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre>\";}}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"cols specification\";s:8:\"children\";a:6:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"col-xsmall-8 title\";s:7:\"content\";s:39:\"<header><h3>Specification</h3></header>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 \";s:7:\"content\";s:13:\"<h3>Name</h3>\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break\";s:7:\"content\";s:190:\"<header><p>Shows the name above the trigger.</p></header><div class=\"row\"><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">string</i></p></div><div class=\"row\"><p>Default <i class=\"lighting\">null</i></p></div>\";}i:3;O:8:\"stdClass\":1:{s:5:\"class\";s:5:\"clear\";}i:4;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 \";s:7:\"content\";s:19:\"<h3>Margin top</h3>\";}i:5;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 \";s:7:\"content\";s:208:\"<header><p>Margin from top allowing adjust moment of call event.</p></header><div class=\"row\"><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">integer</i></p></div><div class=\"row\"><p>Default <i class=\"lighting\">0</i></p></div>\";}}}}}'),
(1000004, 28, 'es_builder_output_backup', 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:4:\"cols\";s:8:\"children\";a:1:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:13:\"col-xsmall-8 \";s:7:\"content\";s:921:\"<h2>Description</h2><p>The function create new scene and it is preparing container of functions which allow you to create actions. The function is connecting all values, target as scene, trigger, selectors and visual. You can use the function by following the example below.</p><pre class=\" language-javascript\"><code class=\" language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> scene <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">enedScroll</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span> @target <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> @trigger <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> @options <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\";}}}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"cols specification\";s:8:\"children\";a:11:{i:0;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:18:\"col-xsmall-8 title\";s:7:\"content\";s:57:\"<p> </p><header><h3>Specification</h3></header><p> </p>\";}i:1;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:25:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 \";s:7:\"content\";s:15:\"<h3>Target</h3>\";}i:2;O:8:\"stdClass\":2:{s:5:\"class\";s:30:\"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break\";s:7:\"content\";s:757:\"<header><p>It is element which is the point of reference for offset and duration. All these values ​​will be suggesting by the target’s properties. E.g. Integer 0 for offset means offset of the target. Above it is described as scene.</p></header><div class=\"row\"><p>Type <i class=\"lighting\">string </i><i class=\"lighting\">object</i></p></div><pre class=\" language-jav