(453, 1, '2023-08-07 17:03:44', '2023-08-07 15:03:44', '  <article data-ix=\"article-15126754343141849\"><div class=\"cols\" data-ix=\"row-151267544602984178\"><div class=\"col-xsmall-8\" data-ix=\"column-151267545108345954\"><div data-ix=\"column-151267545108345954_item\" editor-item=\"\"><h2>License</h2><p>The enedScroll is subject to the license selected when purchasing the product.</p><p><a class=\"inline\" href=\"https://codecanyon.net/licenses/standard\">Read more about Envato licenses</a>&nbsp;</p><p><a class=\"inline\" href=\"https://codecanyon.net/licenses/faq\">FAQ Envato licenses</a></p></div></div></div></article><article data-ix=\"article-15126754421368502\"><div class=\"cols\" data-ix=\"row-151267549484873180\"><div class=\"col-xsmall-8\" data-ix=\"column-151267549764635399\"><div data-ix=\"column-151267549764635399_item\" editor-item=\"\"><h2>Installing</h2><p>To get started with enedScroll you need jQuery version &lt; 1.x.x and enedScroll files.</p><p>Before [markup]&lt;/body&gt;[/markup] tag you should include once of enedScroll version, normall or minifed. You can use code below.</p><p>[code]&lt;script src=\"enedScroll.min.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;[/code]</p></div></div></div></article><article data-ix=\"article-151267544256180038\"><div class=\"cols\" data-ix=\"row-151267555546249998\"><div class=\"col-xsmall-8\" data-ix=\"column-151267555794659229\"><div data-ix=\"column-151267555794659229_item\" editor-item=\"\"><h2 class=\"title\">Trigger</h2><p>This is a magic wand with which you can determine when to call your scene. For a more detailed description of Trigger you will find it here <em><strong>{{ a &gt; trigger - add element }}</strong></em>.</p></div></div></div></article><article data-ix=\"article-151267544297661342\"><div class=\"cols\" data-ix=\"row-151267562192048055\"><div class=\"col-xsmall-8\" data-ix=\"column-151267562499452981\"><div data-ix=\"column-151267562499452981_item\" editor-item=\"\"><h2 class=\"title\">Selectors</h2><p>Selectors as trigger can determine moment to call your event.</p><p>Exists 2 selectors, top and bottom. Specifies a moment of a function call is based on the element that was assigned to the scene as a target.</p></div></div></div></article><article data-ix=\"article-151267544332738019\"><div class=\"cols\" data-ix=\"row-151267565549745184\"><div class=\"col-xsmall-8\" data-ix=\"column-151267565826783913\"><div data-ix=\"column-151267565826783913_item\" editor-item=\"\"><h2 class=\"title\">Scene</h2><p>It is basic space to create animations. All parameters like duration are connected with scene parameters.</p></div></div></div></article>', 'Getting started', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-08-07 17:03:44', '2023-08-07 15:03:44', '', 15, 'http://localhost/enedScroll/docs/?p=453', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
